>Data Normalization
.its scaling numeric features to a standard range, preventing large values from dominating the learning process 
in machine learning 
.ensures that numerical features (in ML and data analysis) are on a similar scale for optimal model performance 
importance:
    .avoids numerical instability in models
    .speeds up convergence in gradient-based algorithms
    .ensures all features contribute equally to the analysis 

    >steps
        .import the required libraries 
        .load or create a dataset 
        .apply different normalization techniques 
        .visualize the results 

    .Normalization techniques 
    1. Maximum absolute scaling 
    .rescales each feature between -1 and 1 by dividing all values by the maximum absolute value in that column 
    .useful when the data doesn't contain negative numbers, and the need to preserve the data's sparcity

    2. min-max feature scaling
    .also called normalization
    .rescales the feature to a hard and fast range of [0,1] by subtracting the min value of the feature then dividing by the range 

    3.z-score method
    .often called standardization
    .changes the values in each column so that they have a mean of 0 and a standard deviation of 1
    .best when the data follows a normal distribution or when I want to treat values in terms of how far they are from the average



