>groupby() method
.splits a dataframe into groups based on one or more columns, allowing for efficient data analysis and aggregation
    .follows a 'split-apply-combine' strategy - data is divided into groups, a function applied to each group, and the results 
    combined into a new dataframe 
        .split - dividing the data into groups based on some criteria; groups defined by unique values in one or more columns
        .apply - apply the function to each group independently
            .applying various functions to each group: 
                .aggregation - calculate summary statistics for each group e.g mean, sum, count
                .transformation - modify the results within each group 
                .filtering - keep or discard groups based on certain conditions 
        .combining - results of the applied function are combined into a new dataframe/series 


Transformation
.transformation functions return an object that is indexed the same as the original group 
    .useful for when applying operations that maintain the original structure of the data e.g normalization
.apply group-specific operations while maintaining the original shape of the dataset 
.unlike aggregation which reduces data, transformations allow group-specific modifications without altering the shape of the data 

.Filtration
.allows me to drop the entire groups from a groupby() object based on a condition
.helps in cleaning data by removing groups that do not meet specific criteria, thus focusing only on relevant subsets 